An IoT Gateway is a device that acts as a bridge between IoT sensor nodes and the cloud. It collects data from multiple sensors, 
processes or filters it if required, converts data between different communication protocols, and securely forwards the information to
cloud platforms. An IoT gateway also improves security, reduces network traffic, and allows communication between devices that use different
technologies.
Diagram
+----------------+      +----------------+      +----------------+      +----------------+
| IoT Sensor     | ---> | IoT Gateway    | ---> | Cloud Platform | ---> | User           |
| Nodes          |      | (ESP32/RPi)    |      |                |      | Application    |
+----------------+      +----------------+      +----------------+      +----------------+
Protocols Used
| Layer                    | Common Protocols           |
| ------------------------ | -------------------------- |
| Sensor Nodes → Gateway   | Zigbee, LoRa, BLE, Wi-Fi   |
| Gateway → Cloud          | MQTT, HTTP/HTTPS, CoAP     |
| Cloud → User Application | HTTPS, WebSocket, REST API |
Conclusion

The IoT gateway enables reliable, secure, and efficient communication between IoT devices and cloud services by managing data flow and 
protocol conversion.
